<item>
            <title>[LU-19323] lnet_selftest.sh support for ipv6 </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19323</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently script only seems to support ipv4 , will need support for ipv6 to help with validation.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@ai400x2-c0-vm00 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lnet_selftest.sh --help&lt;br/&gt;
You need to manually load lnet_selftest on all nodes&lt;br/&gt;
modprobe lnet_selftest&lt;br/&gt;
Invalid option: &amp;#8211;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;usage: lnet_selftest.sh -c client-nids -s server-nids &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-r&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-w&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-n rpcs&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-l size&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-d dist&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-c &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;client nids&lt;br/&gt;
-s &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;server nids&lt;br/&gt;
-r &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;reads only&lt;br/&gt;
-w &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;writes only&lt;br/&gt;
-l size &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; transfer size, defaults to 1M&lt;br/&gt;
-d distribute &#160; distribute, defaults to 1:1&lt;br/&gt;
-n rpcs &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; max_rpcs_in_flight, defaults to 8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;example:&lt;br/&gt;
lnet_selftest.sh -c &quot;10.10.100.223@o2ib 10.10.100.224@o2ib&quot; &#160;-s &quot;10.10.100.215@o2ib 10.10.100.216@o2ib&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
