                            <comment id="471689" author="yujian" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 20:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It turned out sanity-lnet test_228, test_257, and test_270 were added after patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/55422&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/55422&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16822&quot; title=&quot;test IPv6 NIDs in sanity-lnet.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16822&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16822&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: Force IPv6 testing in mixed environment&quot;) was landed. Let me add them into the except list first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471681" author="yujian" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:50:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, Andreas.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471678" author="adilger" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:33:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yujian&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yujian&quot;&gt;yujian&lt;/a&gt;, can you please push a patch to add test_228 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19314&quot; title=&quot;IPv6 sanity-lnet test_228: Can&amp;#39;t find test in current session&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), test_232 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19373&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lnet test_232: lnetctl lnet unconfigure failed 240 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19373&quot;&gt;LU-19373&lt;/a&gt;), test_250 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18135&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lnet test_250: test_250 failed with 1: Error: argument &amp;quot;eth0&amp;quot; is wrong: table id value is invalid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18135&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18135&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), test_257 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19334&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lnet test_257: FAIL: Failed to disable routing rc = 240&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19334&quot;&gt;LU-19334&lt;/a&gt;), and test_270 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19363&quot; title=&quot;IPv6 sanity-lnet test_270: FAIL: Didn&amp;#39;t find metadata reply message in log&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19363&quot;&gt;LU-19363&lt;/a&gt;) to &lt;tt&gt;always_except&lt;/tt&gt; in the &lt;tt&gt;FORCE_LARGE_NID&lt;/tt&gt; section at the start of &lt;tt&gt;sanity-lnet.sh&lt;/tt&gt;.  I guess these are new subtests that were added since IPv6 testing was done, or they started failing more recently?  They were not failing when the list of IPv6 exceptions were added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/55422&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/55422&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16822&quot; title=&quot;test IPv6 NIDs in sanity-lnet.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16822&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16822&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: Force IPv6 testing in mixed environment&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) when it was landed on 2024-07-08.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While some of these subtests are unrelated to lnet-selftest, they all appear to be related to IPv6, so they may as well be added in a single patch, so that these sessions can start passing consistently and be enforced, so that there are no further regressions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="470058" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 4 Sep 2025 18:22:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The reason for the delay on this work is that its different than lnetctl. For lnetctl we can push commands and pull data. For lnet selftest it goes both ways at once so it makes it more complicated. For group handling when groups are created selftest attempts to ping each target to see if they exist. I found Netlink not to be too happy when doing these call outs before finishing up processing the group creation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
